				<!-- HeadlineContent --><div id="HeadlineContent">
		<h1 class="contentHeadline">Transportation and Infrastructure Renewal</h1>
</div>
<!-- /HeadlineContent --><!-- Content -->
	
	<!-- If you need another header under the <H1>, use an <H2> and add the "smallheader" class (the <H2> will look like an <H3>). -->
	We build and maintain quality provincial infrastructure for Nova Scotians. On this site you will find information about <a href="/tran/highways/">highways construction and maintenance</a>, bridges and <a href="/tran/works/">government buildings</a>. You will also learn about our many <a href="/tran/roadsafety/roadsafety.asp">road safety initiatives</a> As of October 20, 2014, the department assumed responsibility for the Registry of Motor Vehicles (RMV) from Service Nova Scotia. The RMV includes programs such as driver licensing, vehicle registration and driving records and compliance Our provincial <a href="/tran/cameras/">highway cameras</a> and the<a href="http://511.gov.ns.ca/en/">511</a>are the main websites in government for up to date information on road conditions.
    



